subject: Re: [junit] TestCase() not public in junit.framework.TestCase
msgSnippet: ... Your test cases do not belong in junit.framework But they have to be public, like in public class SomeTest { } compared to class someTest { } Robert
messageBody:
On Thursday 29 August 2002 06:03, botartist wrote:

> "TestCase() not public in junit.framework.TestCase; cannot be
> accessed from outside package"

Your test cases do not belong in junit.framework
But they have to be public, like in

public class SomeTest {
}

compared to

class someTest {
}

Robert
